Thus in that known place Job 14.14. He reſolves, that all the days of his appointed time, he would wait till his change came. [
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ] All the days of my warfare will I wait, or (as the Verb there alſo ſignifies) will I Hope, or Truſt, till my Change come. Till I change a tumultuous and uncertain World, for a World of Happineſs, and Peace, and Joy, for all Ages.
